  "hypothesis": "REFRAMED H1 (PRIMARY \u2014 Agent B pre-impl caveat 2026-05-11): peak_return captures DIFFERENT information than point_return at H60. Comparing test_ic against each arm's OWN labels is tautological. The PRIMARY gate is BACKTEST P&L (execution-aligned via OpraCalibratedCosts.deep_itm() point-to-point 0DTE Deep ITM). Sub-claims: H1a peak vs point arms produce DIFFERENT backtest P&L with BH FDR q < 0.10 over K=2 paired comparisons (peak-vs-point within each of {ridge, tlob}); H1b effect- size floor |\u0394P&L| > 0.5%; H1c at least 1 arm median |pred| > 1.4 bps. Refuting H1 = closes a research direction (peak_return not tradeable enhancement vs point_return at H60). LABEL-EXECUTION MISMATCH CAVEAT: peak_return is forward-leaking structurally similar to smoothed-vs-point pathology (E8 root cause). R-16a relies on backtest P&L (execution-aligned) NOT test_ic (label- aligned) as the tradability test. H2 (BASELINE GATE): temporal_ridge captures \u226580% of TLOB IC within return_type per CLAUDE.md \u00a7Validated Findings. Required by hft-rules \u00a713. H3 (COST GATE): backtest median |prediction| > 1.4 bps Deep ITM breakeven per OpraCalibratedCosts.deep_itm(). Backtesting stage auto-applies. POWER-LIMITED: 1 seed \u00d7 4 arms; if INDETERMINATE result, plan R-16a- extended (4 arms \u00d7 3 seeds per seed_stability.yaml template).\n",
